race.comment: BAWNAGLEN (1) missed the start then went through his gears nicely to get up for fourth last start over 1200m at Scone when second-up from a break. Peaked last prep when third-up. Needs the extra 200m badly and in a thin field looks a nice bet. BILLABONG ALVIN (4) went back last start over this distance at Dubbo and made some late impression without threatening. Runs his best races when ridden forward and that opportunity arises here. Should give a great sight. NOTERBEL (10) led but was easily accounted for last time out over this distance at Dubbo, recording her third minor placing in a row and fourth overall. Will lead or sit second and is sure to give some cheek. YIASOU (12) led for the judge but found the winner far too good over 1200m at Coonabarabran recently. Very fit after three runs back and shouldn't mind the step up in distance. BROADCAST BOOGIE (5) has placed two from five at today's journey and looks the only other feasible chance.
